.TH "ptm_unix98_lookup" 9 "ptm_unix98_lookup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ptm_unix98_lookup \- find a pty master
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tty_struct *" ptm_unix98_lookup
.BI "(struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct file *file "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
ptm driver
.IP "file" 12
unused
.IP "idx" 12
tty index

Look up a pty master device. Called under the tty_mutex for now.
This provides our locking.
